$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadécimal ezali lolenge ya kolakisa ba données binaire na ndenge oyo moto akoki kotanga. Esalemaki na ekeke ya 19 mpo na kopesa nzela na baordinatɛrɛ ete ebomba makambo mingi.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Okoki kosalela hexadécimal mpo na kobongola kati na motuya ya décimale mpe binaire. Ndakisa, kobongola 10011011001010 na hexadécimal ekosala ete 0x4F ezala. Yango elingi koloba ete motuya 4F ezali komonisa motango ya binaire 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Na matematiki mpe na informatique, hexadécimal (lisusu base 16, to hex) ezali système numérique positionnel na radix, to base, ya 16. Esalelaka bilembo zomi na motoba ekeseni, mingi mingi bilembo 0–9 mpo na komonisa motuya zéro kino libwa, . mpe A, B, C, D, E, F (to na lolenge mosusu a–f) mpo na komonisa motuya zomi kino zomi na mitano. Ndakisa, motango ya hexadécimal 2AF3 ekokani, na décimale, na (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , to 10.995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Chiffre hexadécimal moko na moko ezali komonisa ba chiffres binaire minei (bits) (oyo babengaka yango mpe &quot;nibble&quot;), mpe bosaleli ya liboso ya notation hexadécimal ezali lokola representation ya ba valeurs codées binaire oyo ebongi na bato na informatique mpe na électronique numérique. Ndakisa, motuya ya octet ekoki kozala kobanda 0 kino 255 (décimal) kasi ekoki kozala na lolenge ya malamu koleka lokola ba chiffres hexadécimal mibale na kati ya 00 kino FF. Hexadécimal esalelamaka mpe mingi mpo na komonisa baadrɛsi ya mémoire ya ordinatɛrɛ.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ezali abréviation ya Hexadecimal, oyo esalemi na structure ya base -16 mpe esalelamaka pona ko simplifier ndenge nini ba instructions na ba ordinateurs elakisami. Système oyo ya nombre ya 16 symboles esalemaki lokola moyen ya kopekisa nombre binaire ya 8 bits, yango wana ba données ekoki kozala encodées na ba ordinateurs sans effort. Ekoki ko imprimer mpe ko typer na nzela ya ba chiffres hexagoliques mibale ekeseni na chiffre hexagonal moko na moko oyo ezali kolakisa nibble to peut-être format ya 4 bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Système oyo ya ba nombres esalelaka ba symboles 16 oyo elakisami na intervalle kobanda 0-9 to AF. Ba 0–9 ezali komonisa mituya kino libwa nzokande AF ezali komonisama na mituya 10–15. Soki tokokanisi yango na mitindo misato mosusu ya ba systèmes ya nombre, système ya numérique hexadécimal etalelami lokola oyo eleki malamu.';
